String impressumEnglish = "Declaration according to TMG (Telemediengesetz), §5\n\nEmmy-Noether-Gymnasium\nNoetherstraße 49b\n91058 Erlangen\nGermany\n\nRepresented by:\nStDin Antonie Walther\n\nContact\n\nPhone: +49 (09131) 68776-0\nFax: +49 (09131) 68776-20\nEmail: sekretariat@eng-erlangen.de\n\nSettlement of Disputes/Arbitration\n\nWe are neither willing nor obliged to participate in any consumer protection lawsuit.\n\nLiability for Content\n\nAccording to TMG, §7, 1st paragraph, we as Service Provider are responsible only for the content produced by ourselves. As Service Provider we are according to TMG, §§8-10, in no case obliged neither to monitor nor to supervise Third Party information. We cannot held liable for Third Party information if (but not limited to) such information potentially could indicate illicit intentions of those Third Parties.\nOur liability to remove/delete information and/or to block access to information according to applicable laws and regulations remain in full force. However, our liability for such information won’t start before reception of a written notification regarding a possible infringement. If in such a case it would come to our knowledge that specific content would potentially give reason to consider it as being in legal violation we will block/remove/delete this content promptly.\n\nLiability for provided Links to Third Party websites\n\nThis application contains links to Third Party websites. We do not have any influence to the content of these Third Party websites. Hence, we are under no circumstances liable neither for those Third Party websites nor their content. The content of these Third Party websites is solely the responsibility of the Third Party Service Provider of these websites. Nevertheless, at the point in time when this application was initially published, the linked contents of Third Party websites have been reviewed and checked for possible infringements which could not be detected. A permanent monitoring of the content of Third Party websites cannot be provided and is not reasonable without specific and precise indication of a violation of law. If any potential violation in law caused by a Third Party website would come to our attention we would immediately remove the link to the particular website.\n\nCopyright\n\nThis application and its content is subject to the German Copyright legislation. Any duplication, editing, processing, adaptation, publishing and utilization outside of the limits provided under the German Copyright laws requires written consent, confirmation and release of the author/originator. Downloads and copies of this application are allowed for private use only, any commercial/business use is strictly prohibited.\nAs far as any content was not produced by the provider of this application but from Third Parties, then the Copyright of these Third Parties are respected. Third Party content is marked as such. In case a violation of Copyright would come to our knowledge we will remove/delete this content promptly.\n\nSource:\nhttps://www.e-recht24.de";
